
[1]infidel

   IN'FIDEL, a. [L. infidelis; in and fidelis; faithful.]

   Unbelieving; disbelieving the inspiration of the Scriptures, or the
   divine institution of christianity.

   The infidel writer is a great enemy to society.

   IN'FIDEL, n. One who disbelieves the inspiration of the Scriptures, and
                     the divine origin of christianity.
